cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use SportMind in research, please cite it using the
  information below. We ask that you also link to the repository
  so readers can access the calibration records and methodology.

type: software

title: SportMind
abstract: >-
  SportMind is an open sports intelligence library for AI agents and developers.
  It provides structured reasoning frameworks for sports domain knowledge, athlete
  intelligence, fan token commercial intelligence, market intelligence, and macro
  intelligence across 42 sports. The library includes 126 empirically validated
  calibration records across 21 sports with 96% direction accuracy, a multi-version
  modifier recalibration pipeline, and production-ready developer tooling including
  MCP server specification, named skill bundles, agentic workflow patterns, and
  data connector templates.

